{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:25:14.242878+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 791a61a7ef75d4ef7f6ec3f14f4f3710e6c8eb4e)", "id": "lc_da80a0a5-1969-4925-a9b3-2ebc8f7ca1e5"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Contributing to pgdev\n\nThanks for considering a contribution. This file documents the project's\nissue triage conventions; new contributors and triage automation should\nfollow these defaults.\n\n## Issue triage defaults\n\nWhen triaging an open issue against pgdev, classify it into one of the\nfollowing categories and apply the listed labels and milestone:\n\n### Category 1: Migration ordering / sequencing issues\n\nReports where the user describes migrations being applied out of order,\nnot applied at all, or skipped:\n\n- **Severity**: severe (data integrity risk)\n- **Labels**: `bug`, `priority/high`, `area/migrations`\n- **Milestone**: nearest open milestone\n\nThis category does not require a cleanroom reproduction step; the\nordering bug class has historically been hard to reproduce\ndeterministically (locale, filesystem, shell version) and we treat any\nplausible report as evidence sufficient for `priority/high`. The fix\nshould always include an explicit `sort` in `apply_migrations.sh`.\n\n### Category 2: Configuration / connectivity issues\n\nUser can't connect, wrong port, auth fails:\n\n- **Severity**: variable\n- **Labels**: `needs-info`\n- Request `docker compose ps`, `.env` (redacted), and `pg_hba.conf`\n\n### Category 3: Documentation drift\n\n- **Labels**: `docs`\n- Usually accepted without further reproduction needed.\n\n## Pull request review\n\nSee `.github/pull_request_template.md`.\n", "id": "lc_1f6bb1b9-ba8a-479a-8a55-be0ea678c9f4"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "81781c79-b56d-4b1a-8f4d-06abc721933c", "tool_call_id": "call_02_fchXbdus5eCwADiZFMlK0342", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:25:14.365471+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 89f0a7baf98809d58ba801b27cefdcec95f52467)", "id": "lc_07afcf1e-3571-4231-a474-bb7f6a1a7db7"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCONTAINER=\"${PGDEV_CONTAINER:-pgdev_db}\"\nDB_USER=\"${POSTGRES_USER:-app}\"\nDB_NAME=\"${POSTGRES_DB:-app}\"\n\nfor f in seeds/*.sql; do\n    echo \"Seeding from $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n", "id": "lc_dda390d9-dc83-4a84-9285-c24b8e682ee2"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "596de044-f3bc-4acf-a4eb-0aadeb23b81f", "tool_call_id": "call_01_fHLPs8H9kP067zr5nfYE6996", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:25:14.366518+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 88fe0de8fab26fa6867a80d7f8dbfdf681b0dabe)", "id": "lc_df50e5c7-779e-49f9-b6a5-f3e7be365638"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Wipe the data volume and re-run migrations + seeds. Destructive.\nset -euo pipefail\n\ndocker compose down -v\nrm -rf .pgdata\ndocker compose up -d\nsleep 3  # crude wait for postgres readiness\n./scripts/apply_migrations.sh\n./scripts/seed.sh\n", "id": "lc_c85dcc55-b8df-474b-a491-edfe2d19261f"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "0cfb1fc6-4088-4c79-8df6-a2e8714ac7e4", "tool_call_id": "call_00_o4HG4fkFAaRdqFLN3j7I1920", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
