{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:25:20.730193+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"issues\":[{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"apply_migrations.sh applies files in wrong order on filesystems with case-folding\",\"body\":\"Hi — I think I found an ordering bug in `scripts/apply_migrations.sh`.\\n\\nOn my workstation (macOS, default APFS, `LC_COLLATE=en_US.UTF-8`), running `./scripts/apply_migrations.sh` from a fresh checkout sometimes applies `003_add_session_index.sql` before `002_create_sessions.sql`. That fails because the index targets a table that hasn\\u0026#39;t been created yet.\\n\\nMy best guess: the script relies on `for f in migrations/*.sql; do` which uses shell glob expansion, and APFS being case-insensitive plus a non-C locale messes with the sort order in zsh on some Apple builds.\\n\\nReproducer:\\n  1. Fresh checkout\\n  2. docker compose up -d\\n  3. ./scripts/apply_migrations.sh\\n\\nResult: psql complains \\u0026#34;relation \\\\\\u0026#34;sessions\\\\\\u0026#34; does not exist\\u0026#34; while applying 003.\\n\\nWorkaround I\\u0026#39;m using locally: replace the loop with\\n  `for f in $(ls migrations/*.sql | sort); do`\\n\\nHappy to send a PR if a sorted-explicit loop is acceptable.\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\"},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:03:42Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:03:42Z\"}],\"totalCount\":1,\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":false,\"hasPreviousPage\":false,\"startCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMzo0MlrPAAAAAQwoX-o=\",\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMzo0MlrPAAAAAQwoX-o=\"}}", "id": "lc_d12e1675-beb7-4509-8ff2-9526e6c703c7"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "list_issues", "id": "30c1f7c5-2958-4f12-bc61-933704ce8e61", "tool_call_id": "call_00_z5NlznuUIIhtUw6upSjr3645", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:25:27.349544+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 576, "prompt_tokens": 9059, "total_tokens": 9635, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 169, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8576}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8576, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 483}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "67e0b8f1-d01f-4698-91d6-142e67bbb5cb", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f9-d8db-7951-9c3d-60f83e3db9fd-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "issue_write", "args": {"method": "update", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T11_R01_C03_A02", "issue_number": 1, "labels": ["bug", "priority/high", "area/migrations"], "body": "Thank you for the detailed report, @BruceKZ. You've correctly identified a real issue with shell glob ordering on case-insensitive filesystems when the locale collation differs from the byte-by-byte sort order the migration filenames assume.\n\nThis matches **Category 1 (Migration ordering / sequencing issues)** per `CONTRIBUTING.md`. We treat this as `priority/high` because:\n- It can cause silent partial migration (or outright failure) in development.\n- It's hard to reproduce deterministically (depends on locale, filesystem, shell version).\n- The fix is well-understood: introduce an explicit `sort` step.\n\nThe preferred fix is to replace the loop with something like:\n```bash\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n```\nwith an explicit sort, e.g.:\n```bash\nfor f in $(printf '%s\\n' migrations/*.sql | sort); do\n```\n(We tend to avoid `ls` parsing in scripts as a matter of style — `printf` is more portable and doesn't have the quoting pitfalls.)\n\nIf you'd like to open a PR with that change, we'd be happy to review it. Otherwise, we'll pick this up in an upcoming sprint.\n\nThank you again for the thorough investigation!"}, "id": "call_00_fstBC79s8Z6hwOd61hOF8767", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9059, "output_tokens": 576, "total_tokens": 9635, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 8576}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 169}}}}]}}}
